		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Feb 27th 11:39 AM 2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=98328804455438&num=4&post=1&replyto=98329198557156"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=98329198557156></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=2300"><span id=Scholar>DrophWayseeker</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br>44 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Ideally, you want to keep all your weapon skills maxxed out. You will want 1HS for when you<br>acquire a Ghoulbane, and 2HS for when you start thinking about the quest swords. For your level, a shiny brass shield is fine. It's magic, which would allow you to bash willowisps and any other MOBs that can only be hit by magic weapons. It also gives light like a GLS, which is nice<br>if you have bad night vision (it frees up a slot that you've had to carry a lightsource in). Bash will never do as much damage as your weapons. Later on when your skill is better, one of the<br>primary things you will use bash for is to stun opponents (disrupting spellcasting, stopping them from fleeing, etc.). I am a level 40 paladin, and I use 1HS/shield as well as 2HS.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Feb 27th 11:51 AM 2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=98328804455438&num=4&post=1&replyto=98329271057092"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=98329271057092></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>At your level and your location, you can very easily upgrade your shield to a better one.&nbsp;&nbsp;In Crushbone, go to the trainer's hill and kill the Orc Trainer.  On him, there is a Shiny Brass Shield (12AC, +10svmagic....forgot the rest of the stats, but it is a lightsource).  I think it is a fairly rare drop so you may have to kill him a few times before you actually get one. (I lucked out and got mine on teh first kill, as a result of killing him after a train to the entrance).  After about lvl 21, you can obtain the Cracked Darkwood Shield on Highpass Hold off of a named Gnoll (again I forgot to name).  I'm not sure how bash is determined, although logically it would be determined by the amount of AC the shield has.   <br><br> A 2HS weapon that would be nice to pick up is an Axe of the Iron Back (16dmg, 38dly)- true the damage isn't that wonderful but the delay allows you to learn that skill quickly.  Something I really suggest learning at an earlier lvl,  as at lvl 40 I am just now learning to use a 1HB weapon and grow very frustrtated with teh amount of time I have to put in using that type of weapon before I advance on skill lvl.<br><br>As far as the Ghoulbane goes, it is one of the best 1HS weapons in the game at the level in which you can get it.  And, it is essential if you plan on completing the Epic Quests later on in the game for your Fiery Avenger (and later Fiery Defender)- btw these are both 2HS swords.<br><br>Dadin Holyshroud<br>40th season and loyal follower of Brell Selleris<br>&lt;The House Saban&gt;<br>Xev Server</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
